1. diff b/w document and windows object?
  answer: *  Document object represents the whole html document as a tree of Objects(HTML, HEAD, BODY, and other HTML tags). 
             It is the root element that represents the html document.
          *  The window object represents a window/tab containing a DOM document where as document object is property of window object that points to the 
             DOM document loaded in that window You can access a document object either using window.document property or using document object directly as 
             window is global object
